article.headline: Colgate 64, Army 42
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- Yaw Gyawu scored 15 points and grabbed a six rebounds, leading Colgate to a 64-42 win over Army Saturday in the Patriot League opener for both teams. Mike Venezia scored 10 points for the Raiders (5-9, 1-0), while Anthony Hill and Ben Jonson added nine apiece. Colgate shot 52 percent from the field, while holding Army to 27 percent. Julian Simmons led Army with 13 points, while Jeremy Hence added six points and grabbed seven rebounds for the Black Knights. Colgate broke away from an 8-8 tie at 17:24 in the first half with an 8-0 run that opened up a lead that it would not relinquish. Willie Morse and Hill started the run with a pair of 3-pointers, and Venezia added the final basket. Colgate quickly extended its lead to 20 points at the start of the second half and led by as many as 25 points with 5:49 left to play.
